## What We're Building Next (Phase 2+)

### 🔧 Backend — Next Phase

| Priority | Item | Details |
|----------|------|---------|
| P0 | Testing suite | Unit tests (Vitest) for PR detection, EMA algorithm, streak calc, intent classifier. Integration tests (Supertest + real MySQL) for API routes. E2E (Playwright) for critical user flows. |
| P0 | Redis dashboard caching | Cache `getDashboardSummary` response with TTL, invalidate on new data entry. Target: 800ms → 45ms. |
| P1 | EXPLAIN ANALYZE optimization | Composite indexes on hot query paths. Target: dashboard query 340ms → 12ms. |
| P1 | GraphQL AI Chat subscription | Stream AI responses via GraphQL subscription for real-time status indicators |
| P2 | Bundle splitting | React.lazy() code splitting. Target: 420KB → 180KB initial bundle. |
| P2 | API compression | Gzip on all text responses via Nginx. Target: 80% reduction. |

### 🤖 AI — Next Phase

| Priority | Item | Details |
|----------|------|---------|
| P0 | Streaming responses | SSE or GraphQL streaming for real-time token delivery to the frontend |
| P1 | Web Search enrichment | Tavily Search API for questions needing external knowledge ("is 5:10/km good for a beginner?") |
| P1 | Context plan viewer | Collapsible panel per message showing which tools were called, token usage, response time |
| P1 | New tools | `logWeight`, `logHabits`, `getRunSummary`, `getProgressReport` |
| P2 | Pipeline trace storage | Save tool-call sequence, token counts, execution time per conversation to `ai_conversations` table |
| P1 | LLM-as-Judge evaluation | Automated quality scoring of agent responses — a second LLM call grades relevance, accuracy, and safety of the coach's output. Enables regression testing and prompt tuning without manual review. |
